inks early life career phil fish born philippe poisson[2] montreal 1984.[3] raised quebec, parents shared interest art gaming him. fish's father translated legend zelda french two could play together. fish credits memories formative, later cited influence fez.[2] graduated 2004 design digital art video games program montreal nad (national animation design centre).[4] fish began career video game publisher ubisoft,[2] worked open season level designer.[5] initially excited job grew disenchanted large development teams working conditions. fish later described "the worst experience [his] life". later fired company.[2] may 24, 2006, fish artificial mind movement award best cut-scene annual nad center awards excellence gala.[6][7] later year, fish began work level designer artificial mind movement,[8] designed film tie-in games[2] including golden compass.[9] fish founding member kokoromi, group designs[3] promotes experimental video games.[10] november 2006 arcadia festival event, gamma 01 audio feed, featured games incorporated live sound.[8] fish planned similar event, gamma 256,[8] 2007, third event, gamma 3d, november 2008 montreal.[11] fish invited present lecture gamma 01 2007 game developers conference.[8] also wrote review 1999 legacy kain: soul reaver 2007 book space time play: synergies computer games, architecture urbanism: next level.[3] additionally, fish characterized sean hollister verge "notorious voicing angry, controversial opinions state video games".[12] polytron see also: development fez fish left artificial mind movement set polytron corporation, indie startup company fish began work toronto-based indie developer shawn mcgrath mcgrath's idea puzzle game showed 2d views 3d space. fish provided project's art[2] partnership crumbled due creative differences: fish wanted product platform game.[13] fish continued work game spare time,[2] incorporated idea voxels (3d pixels), 2d pixel could seen four sides. game would become fez game's design, lore, art derived game mechanic. fish searched programmer deviantart renaud bédard, first person apply, became game's programmer.[13] fez first announced july 2007[14] nominated two awards 2008 game developers conference independent games festival.[15] fish's employer, artificial mind movement, would let take leave work attend, fish quit. marked january 2008 moment "when became indie". game received widespread attention upon showing festival, leading fish open polytron corporation startup company government loan.[2] polytron later ran money[16] verge folding company's québécois neighbor, developer-producer trapdoor, offered help polytron without transferring intellectual property rights. according fish, partnership saved fez.[17] game delayed several times next years[18] received some notoriety.[19] late 2009, polytron presented iphone game called power pill pecha kucha montreal. game features panacean pill travels human bodies playable protagonist, uses iphone's multi-touch screen. gamesetwatch's eric caoili compared soul bubbles irritating stick. game developed alec holowka infinite ammo, level editor expected included.[20] working fez, fish revived game project called super hypercube, based wiimote motion capture input stereoscopic navigation. fish felt game would work better new kinect motion tracking. adapted game finalist indiecade 2011.[17] fez development team 2012 gdc igf (from left): composer rich vreeland, designer phil fish, sound designer brandon mccartin, programmer renaud bédard fish fez featured prominently 2012 documentary indie game: movie, fish received celebrity unusual game developers.[21] film chronicles stories several indie developers various stages games' development cycles, fish shown preparing fez's booth pax east march 2011. film presents fish amidst legal dispute former business partner jeopardizes game's release.[22] partner, believed jason degroot, portrayed negatively participate onscreen.[23] film also tracks fish's personal emotional investment game. eurogamer wrote part fish resolves kill release game "the film's startling moment".[22] rock, paper, shotgun wrote fish portrayed melodramatic, theatrical, neurotic, film exacerbate outspoken public perception.[24] game informer called fish film's "most memorable developer".[25] film's end credits later revised reflect fish's business partner asked input.[23] near end development, fish felt "burnt out" personal health suffered.[17] fez released april 13, 2012 sold 200,000 copies yearlong exclusivity xbox live arcade platform.[26] video game review aggregator metacritic described reviews 2012 xbox 360 fez "generally favorable"[27] 2013 pc version "universal acclaim".[28] development, fez 2012 gdc independent games festival's seamus mcnally grand prize,[29] 2011 indiecade best show best story/world design,[30] 2008 gdc independent games festival's excellence visual art.[2] eurogamer awarded fez perfect score[31] named "perfect, wordless sci-fi parable" 2012 game year.[32] fish announced eventual ports "'pretty much' every platform" nintendo 3ds.[33] sold one million copies end 2013.[34] new york times's chris suellentrop called fish "a quentin tarantino 8-bit gaming".[35] fez 2 cancelled. done. take money run. much stomach. isn't result one thing, end long, bloody campaign. win. “ ” fez 2 cancellation post polytron's website[36] fez sequel announced "one thing" end horizon indie game press conference june 2013 electronic entertainment expo.[37] twitter argument fish gametrailers journalist marcus beer month later culminated project's cancellation fish's exit industry. episode show invisible walls, beer criticized fish's recent response questions microsoft's xbox one self-publishing policy change. twitter, fish condemned industry negativity final tweet announced cancellation leave.[36] news came surprise rest polytron,[38] commented upcoming projects other ports since sequel's cancellation.[39] polygon listed fish top 50 newsmakers 2013 social power "caustic u